<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Just for noting - node-gyp</title><link href="https://blog.fkz.tw/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="https://blog.fkz.tw/feeds/tag.node-gyp.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>https://blog.fkz.tw/</id><updated>2017-09-01T16:25:08+08:00</updated><subtitle></subtitle><entry><title>Error: contextify@0.1.15 install: `node-gyp rebuild`</title><link href="https://blog.fkz.tw/posts/2017/09/01/error-contextify-0-1-15-install-node-gyp-rebuild/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2017-09-01T16:25:08+08:00</published><updated>2017-09-01T16:25:08+08:00</updated><author><name>fkz</name></author><id>tag:blog.fkz.tw,2017-09-01:/posts/2017/09/01/error-contextify-0-1-15-install-node-gyp-rebuild/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Note for solution of "Error: contextify@0.1.15 install: &lt;code&gt;node-gyp rebuild&lt;/code&gt;"&lt;/p&gt;</summary><content type="html">&lt;h2&gt;Preface&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Encountered this error of one build on Travis CI of some project.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Downgrade node to 6.11 which is LTS version can solve this problem.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="err"&gt;- nvm install v6.11.2  &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;- nvm use v6.11.2  &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Add these two lines into &lt;code&gt;install&lt;/code&gt; part of &lt;code&gt;.travis.yml&lt;/code&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
